- Yes.

316
00:12:25,620 --> 00:12:25,982
Okay.

317
00:12:25,999 --> 00:12:27,119
I'll do it.

318
00:12:27,119 --> 00:12:28,680
Here, don't chop it yet.

319
00:12:28,680 --> 00:12:30,879
No. Why are you here?

320
00:12:31,359 --> 00:12:33,359
No, your chicken is whole.

321
00:12:33,359 --> 00:12:35,119
The one I bought...

322
00:12:35,560 --> 00:12:38,359
Look, I had the supermarket chop it.

323
00:12:38,839 --> 00:12:40,160
Mine is free-range chicken.

324
00:12:40,400 --> 00:12:41,839
Mine is also free-range chicken.

325
00:12:46,639 --> 00:12:47,160
Well...

326
00:12:47,239 --> 00:12:48,479
Both of you go rest.

327
00:12:48,560 --> 00:12:49,160
I'll handle it.

328
00:12:49,160 --> 00:12:50,080
- No need.
- No need.

329
00:12:50,759 --> 00:12:51,519
Mingzhu.

330
00:12:52,320 --> 00:12:52,920
Go rest.

331
00:12:52,920 --> 00:12:53,999
Listen to your mother-in-law.

332
00:12:53,999 --> 00:12:54,879
Yes, go.

333
00:12:54,879 --> 00:12:55,440
You...

334
00:12:55,440 --> 00:12:55,999
Well...

335
00:12:56,639 --> 00:12:57,960
Mrs. Shen, you usually

336
00:12:57,960 --> 00:12:59,719
work hard taking care of them.

337
00:12:59,999 --> 00:13:02,680
Today, please have a rest.

338
00:13:02,680 --> 00:13:03,320
I'll do it.

339
00:13:03,560 --> 00:13:04,560
You enjoy yourself.

340
00:13:04,560 --> 00:13:05,759
Let me serve you all.

341
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:09,800
Give this to me.

342
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:10,400
The apron.

343
00:13:14,599 --> 00:13:15,400
Okay, thanks.

344
00:13:17,400 --> 00:13:18,080
Mrs. Shen.

345
00:13:18,680 --> 00:13:20,200
Come, sit here.

346
00:13:22,280 --> 00:13:22,879
Dacheng.

347
00:13:23,239 --> 00:13:24,920
Don't just stand there in a daze.

348
00:13:24,920 --> 00:13:25,359
Coming.

349
00:13:25,359 --> 00:13:26,519
Take it out.

350
00:13:26,999 --> 00:13:27,920
There's more.

351
00:13:27,920 --> 00:13:29,160
Why did you buy so many groceries?

352
00:13:29,160 --> 00:13:31,040
Yeah, we came to bring you groceries,

353
00:13:31,040 --> 00:13:31,879
you know?

354
00:13:31,960 --> 00:13:33,200
To nourish your body.

355
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:34,519
Yes, nourish your body.

356
00:13:37,115 --> 00:13:37,960
Making stewed chicken.

357
00:13:37,999 --> 00:13:38,879
Got the floor dirty.

358
00:13:39,080 --> 00:13:40,239
It's okay.

359
00:13:40,759 --> 00:13:41,359
No problem.

360
00:13:42,560 --> 00:13:43,519
Xiang, look.

361
00:13:44,479 --> 00:13:45,239
It's big.

362
00:13:45,479 --> 00:13:46,119
Yeah.

363
00:13:46,440 --> 00:13:47,960
Looks like a boy.

364
00:13:48,440 --> 00:13:49,320
Definitely a boy.

365
00:13:49,320 --> 00:13:49,879
Yes.

366
00:13:49,879 --> 00:13:51,280
But I like girls.

367
00:13:51,280 --> 00:13:52,119
Both are good.

368
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:52,920
Yes.

369
00:13:52,920 --> 00:13:54,604
- Both are good.
- Both are the same.

370
00:13:54,700 --> 00:13:56,422
(No. 68, Wenzhong Avenue, Xidi Road,)

371
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:58,515
(Old Town District, Nanzhou City.
March 26, 1994)

372
00:14:08,040 --> 00:14:09,680
How are you? You're doing well.

373
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:11,359
Good, all good.

374
00:14:11,599 --> 00:14:12,479
Good.

375
00:14:12,839 --> 00:14:14,639
Don't stand here. Go quickly.

376
00:14:14,639 --> 00:14:16,239
Go be with your mother-in-law.

377
00:14:16,239 --> 00:14:17,479
Yes, go rest.

378
00:14:17,479 --> 00:14:18,479
We'll do things here.

379
00:14:18,479 --> 00:14:19,400
Come, Mingzhu.

380
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:20,519
Come rest a bit.

381
00:14:20,759 --> 00:14:22,560
- Go.
- Have a rest.

382
00:14:35,800 --> 00:14:39,839
A mother teaches her son
to serve the country.

383
00:14:40,719 --> 00:14:43,879
With unwavering loyalty.

384
00:14:43,879 --> 00:14:46,080
A mother teaches her son

385
00:14:47,160 --> 00:14:49,200
to honor his parents.

386
00:14:50,080 --> 00:14:52,800
To be

387
00:14:53,479 --> 00:14:56,200
a dutiful and loyal man.

388
00:14:56,440 --> 00:14:59,519
Now that I have become an official.

389
00:15:00,080 --> 00:15:07,280
My mother cannot see it.

390
00:15:21,879 --> 00:15:26,920
- Oh Mother.
- Oh Mother.

391
00:15:28,320 --> 00:15:29,999
What have you been doing lately?

392
00:15:31,239 --> 00:15:33,239
Going around rewinding

393
00:15:33,479 --> 00:15:35,080
this old recorder nonstop.

394
00:15:35,320 --> 00:15:36,479
What recorder?

395
00:15:37,830 --> 00:15:39,004
This is an old cassette.

396
00:15:39,719 --> 00:15:40,560
"Zhu Hen Ji".

397
00:15:40,660 --> 00:15:42,160
You still remember this opera, right?

398
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:43,400
The part at the grave mound.

399
00:15:44,719 --> 00:15:45,440
It's strange.

400
00:15:45,440 --> 00:15:46,960
These past couple of days,

401
00:15:47,893 --> 00:15:49,937
I can't stop thinking about this part.

402
00:15:50,239 --> 00:15:51,280
It won't leave my mind.

403
00:15:52,599 --> 00:15:56,359
They say when you get old,
you start thinking about the past.

404
00:15:56,999 --> 00:15:59,440
You're getting older and missing home.

405
00:15:59,920 --> 00:16:01,648
It's hard to leave our homeland.

406
00:16:02,119 --> 00:16:03,759
In a blink, we've been in the south

407
00:16:04,479 --> 00:16:05,759
for almost 30 years.

408
00:16:07,519 --> 00:16:08,879
Over 30 years...

409
00:16:09,599 --> 00:16:11,040
Our daughter is thirty now.

410
00:16:12,440 --> 00:16:13,080
The other day,

411
00:16:13,360 --> 00:16:15,982
do you remember that customer
ordered sweet and sour pork?

412
00:16:16,359 --> 00:16:17,839
I said, what's so hard about it?

413
00:16:19,440 --> 00:16:20,759
But when I made it,

414
00:16:21,599 --> 00:16:23,839
I just felt it wasn't quite the same.

415
00:16:24,680 --> 00:16:26,719
We've been making braised pork chops

416
00:16:28,239 --> 00:16:29,999
and forgotten the taste of home.

417
00:16:30,879 --> 00:16:31,519
Honey.

418
00:16:32,999 --> 00:16:33,839
Honestly,

419
00:16:35,680 --> 00:16:37,960
all these years we've gone from
a small shop

420
00:16:38,239 --> 00:16:39,680
to now this

421
00:16:40,719 --> 00:16:41,960
big restaurant.

422
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:46,426
It hasn't been easy.

423
00:16:47,920 --> 00:16:49,359
I'm really grateful to you.

424
00:16:49,839 --> 00:16:51,160
Grateful to me for what?

425
00:16:51,160 --> 00:16:52,800
Without you, could I have done it?

426
00:16:53,200 --> 00:16:54,271
No matter how capable I am,

427
00:16:54,519 --> 00:16:55,920
I couldn't have done it alone.

428
00:16:56,280 --> 00:16:56,800
Forget it.

429
00:16:56,800 --> 00:16:58,400
Without you, I can't do anything.

430
00:16:59,999 --> 00:17:02,200
You see, any difficult thing for us,

431
00:17:02,599 --> 00:17:03,160
right?

432
00:17:03,519 --> 00:17:04,319
Once we talk,

433
00:17:05,039 --> 00:17:06,999
it never lasts overnight.

434
00:17:07,400 --> 00:17:07,999
Right?

435
00:17:08,400 --> 00:17:09,079
You are

436
00:17:09,079 --> 00:17:10,920
sometimes nagging,

437
00:17:11,360 --> 00:17:13,880
but what you say is always practical.

438
00:17:13,999 --> 00:17:15,759
Never deceived me or lied to me.

439
00:17:16,680 --> 00:17:17,360
You see,

440
00:17:17,360 --> 00:17:19,319
our life is just harmonious and happy.

441
00:17:20,640 --> 00:17:22,479
We just live our life this way.

442
00:17:26,120 --> 00:17:26,880
I just think...

443
00:17:28,719 --> 00:17:29,640
When will we

444
00:17:33,079 --> 00:17:34,279
pass it on to the kids?

445
00:17:36,848 --> 00:17:38,204
Like leaves returning to roots.

446
00:17:38,204 --> 00:17:39,671
Sometimes I really want to go home.

447
00:17:40,200 --> 00:17:42,519
What about the kids?

448
00:17:42,880 --> 00:17:45,039
Kids? What's there to worry about?

449
00:17:45,960 --> 00:17:48,029
Mingzhu helps Minghui.

450
00:17:48,030 --> 00:17:49,915
Minghui can handle things
on his own now.

451
00:17:50,079 --> 00:17:52,719
He can flip woks and cook dishes
by himself.

452
00:17:53,239 --> 00:17:54,600
Once Mingzhu joins,

453
00:17:54,719 --> 00:17:56,039
the two of them

454
00:17:56,071 --> 00:17:58,160
will surely run the restaurant
better than we do.

455
00:17:59,880 --> 00:18:01,239
Why are you crying?

456
00:18:01,239 --> 00:18:01,960
Shen.

457
00:18:05,200 --> 00:18:06,440
What's this about?

458
00:18:06,840 --> 00:18:07,680
There's something

459
00:18:09,319 --> 00:18:10,440
I've wronged you,

460
00:18:10,440 --> 00:18:11,680
and wronged Mingzhu.

461
00:18:15,200 --> 00:18:17,079
What the heck are you talking about?

462
00:18:19,500 --> 00:18:22,277
(No. 68, Wenzhong Avenue, Xidi Road,)

463
00:18:22,301 --> 00:18:24,820
(Old Town District, Nanzhou City.
March 26, 1994)

464
00:18:27,999 --> 00:18:28,840
I'm sorry.

465
00:18:36,120 --> 00:18:36,519
Dad.

466
00:18:36,799 --> 00:18:38,239
Your mom has something to tell you.

467
00:18:40,719 --> 00:18:41,120
Sit here.

468
00:18:42,360 --> 00:18:42,960
Well...

469
00:18:43,840 --> 00:18:45,680
You sit here.

470
00:18:46,200 --> 00:18:46,840
I'll sit here?

471
00:18:46,840 --> 00:18:47,759
You just sit here.

472
00:18:49,799 --> 00:18:50,640
About what?

473
00:18:51,759 --> 00:18:52,479
Go ahead.

474
00:18:53,440 --> 00:18:54,319
Tired?

475
00:18:55,319 --> 00:18:55,999
Not tired.

476
00:18:57,750 --> 00:18:58,937
There's been something

477
00:18:59,880 --> 00:19:02,840
on her mind all these years.

478
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:04,680
It's been 30 years.

479
00:19:06,680 --> 00:19:07,279
She...

480
00:19:09,600 --> 00:19:10,960
Just speak. Don't make me say it.

481
00:19:10,960 --> 00:19:12,799
I'm so clumsy with words.

482
00:19:14,640 --> 00:19:15,239
It's just...

483
00:19:17,160 --> 00:19:19,120
Do you remember that day at the market,

484
00:19:20,079 --> 00:19:23,120
your birth mother and I

485
00:19:24,519 --> 00:19:25,279
had an argument?

486
00:19:25,279 --> 00:19:26,999
You asked me something.

487
00:19:26,999 --> 00:19:30,120
You asked if there was a note...

488
00:19:32,319 --> 00:19:35,039
You know, from the day
we brought you home,

489
00:19:35,039 --> 00:19:36,840
your dad and I never felt

490
00:19:36,840 --> 00:19:38,293
that you were someone else's child.

491
00:19:38,337 --> 00:19:38,804
Yes.

492
00:19:38,960 --> 00:19:41,479
We just felt you and Minghui
were both ours.

493
00:19:42,479 --> 00:19:43,120
However...

494
00:19:45,840 --> 00:19:46,799
The note

495
00:19:48,319 --> 00:19:48,960
exists.

496
00:19:50,880 --> 00:19:52,479
I didn't tell you the truth.

497
00:19:59,080 --> 00:20:00,861
(No. 68, Wenzhong Avenue, Xidi Road,)

498
00:20:00,885 --> 00:20:03,000
(Old Town District, Nanzhou City.
March 26, 1994)

499
00:20:03,479 --> 00:20:05,239
Actually, I didn't know
about this either.

500
00:20:06,479 --> 00:20:07,640
I just found out too.

501
00:20:07,920 --> 00:20:09,519
Yes, it's all my fault, really.

502
00:20:10,120 --> 00:20:10,920
It's me.

503
00:20:11,920 --> 00:20:13,120
Back then, I just...

504
00:20:13,479 --> 00:20:14,799
When your maternal grandmother

505
00:20:14,799 --> 00:20:16,200
brought you here...

506
00:20:16,200 --> 00:20:17,799
They had given birth to twins.

507
00:20:17,920 --> 00:20:19,239
She kept the boy,

508
00:20:19,239 --> 00:20:20,960
and gave away the girl.

509
00:20:20,960 --> 00:20:23,559
Those were especially difficult years.

510
00:20:23,559 --> 00:20:25,840
I also thought about sending you back.

511
00:20:25,840 --> 00:20:27,239
Later, I thought that their family

512
00:20:27,515 --> 00:20:29,160
must have been very son-preferential.

513
00:20:29,160 --> 00:20:30,671
I was afraid that if you went there,

514
00:20:31,479 --> 00:20:32,200
you would suffer.

515
00:20:33,479 --> 00:20:36,440
So I thought I'd wait for some time.

516
00:20:37,319 --> 00:20:38,719
Time really passes so fast.

517
00:20:38,719 --> 00:20:39,840
In the blink of an eye,

518
00:20:40,640 --> 00:20:41,640
you're...

519
00:20:42,079 --> 00:20:42,840
Becoming a Mother.

520
00:20:42,840 --> 00:20:44,640
You're almost a Mother now.

521
00:20:45,079 --> 00:20:46,840
The further I get, the more

522
00:20:48,319 --> 00:20:48,960
I don't dare.

523
00:20:50,640 --> 00:20:52,840
I'm just afraid

524
00:20:53,640 --> 00:20:56,039
that after hiding this from you
for so many years,

525
00:20:57,400 --> 00:21:00,160
if you got angry and went to find them,

526
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:02,200
we would really

527
00:21:03,120 --> 00:21:03,960
lose you.

528
00:21:03,960 --> 00:21:05,680
That's what I was really afraid of.

529
00:21:06,999 --> 00:21:08,160
- Mom.
- Sorry, my daughter.

530
00:21:08,319 --> 00:21:09,559
Don't say that.

531
00:21:10,840 --> 00:21:13,239
I know how you treated me growing up.

532
00:21:14,880 --> 00:21:16,559
Even though you adopted me,

533
00:21:17,440 --> 00:21:19,120
I have everything Minghui has,

534
00:21:19,515 --> 00:21:21,360
and I even have
what Minghui doesn't have.

535
00:21:21,920 --> 00:21:23,039
I know how you treated me.

536
00:21:23,239 --> 00:21:24,559
I've always known.

537
00:21:24,920 --> 00:21:27,200
I've always considered you
my real parents.

538
00:21:29,559 --> 00:21:30,600
Without you,

539
00:21:30,840 --> 00:21:33,079
I wouldn't be the Shen Mingzhu
I am today.

540
00:21:35,400 --> 00:21:37,960
Actually, this matter...

541
00:21:38,893 --> 00:21:39,982
I hadn't thought it through.

542
00:21:40,048 --> 00:21:41,750
Now we've also figured it out.

543
00:21:42,680 --> 00:21:43,400
You see, we...

544
00:21:44,440 --> 00:21:45,200
For what purpose?

545
00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:47,039
Wasn't it just
to make sure you live well?

546
00:21:47,960 --> 00:21:50,920
You'd have an extra Mom and Dad
to take care of you.

547
00:21:50,920 --> 00:21:51,680
Isn't that great?

548
00:21:52,680 --> 00:21:54,680
If we get sick or disaster strikes,

549
00:21:54,680 --> 00:21:56,559
when we're gone, you'd still have

550
00:21:56,582 --> 00:21:58,826
someone to take care of you.
Isn't that a good thing?

551
00:21:59,519 --> 00:21:59,999
So...

552
00:21:59,999 --> 00:22:00,920
Your mom...

553
00:22:00,920 --> 00:22:02,360
Whenever your mom speaks...

554
00:22:02,799 --> 00:22:04,719
Who could get sick or a disaster strike?

555
00:22:04,920 --> 00:22:07,079
No one can live forever, right?

556
00:22:07,279 --> 00:22:07,920
Right?

557
00:22:08,400 --> 00:22:09,559
Don't say that.

558
00:22:09,719 --> 00:22:10,400
Mingzhu.

559
00:22:11,120 --> 00:22:14,680
As long as you live well,

560
00:22:15,920 --> 00:22:16,719
we can accept

561
00:22:18,239 --> 00:22:19,479
any love.

562
00:22:19,479 --> 00:22:20,719
Yes. The more, the better.

563
00:22:21,079 --> 00:22:22,479
We just hope you're happy.

564
00:22:23,719 --> 00:22:25,719
If you're happy, we're happy.

565
00:22:26,440 --> 00:22:27,160
Dad, Mom.

566
00:22:28,840 --> 00:22:30,440
You will always be my parents.

567
00:22:32,719 --> 00:22:33,960
You two can't escape now.

